{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012tPe7osZDXL3tPuXRUXWHq","type":"tool_result","content":"   273→| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   274→|-------|--------------|---------|\n   275→| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   276→| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   277→| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   278→\n   279→Additionally, `host.cloche` may define a **`release-task`** utility workflow. This is\n   280→not part of the automatic orchestration loop — it is invoked on demand (e.g. from the\n   281→web dashboard) to release a stale claimed task back to `open` status. A task is\n   282→considered stale when it has `in_progress` status but no active worker is running for\n   283→it (e.g. after a failed run or daemon restart). The workflow receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`.\n   284→\n   285→Only `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\n   286→mode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n   287→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a1eb545-c5fc-4d99-8df4-f479f783e58f","uuid":"e9fe6cfb-006c-4241-84e0-9621ae9e473b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n\nAdditionally, `host.cloche` may define a **`release-task`** utility workflow. This is\nnot part of the automatic orchestration loop — it is invoked on demand (e.g. from the\nweb dashboard) to release a stale claimed task back to `open` status. A task is\nconsidered stale when it has `in_progress` status but no active worker is running for\nit (e.g. after a failed run or daemon restart). The workflow receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`.\n\nOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\nmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n","numLines":15,"startLine":273,"totalLines":920}}}
